SIMPLE: trooper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trooper
<hw>Troop"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A soldier in a body of
cavalry; a cavalryman; also, the horse of a cavalryman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state police officer; -- also called
<altname>state trooper</altname>.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A mounted policeman.</def> <mark>[Australia]</mark>
<note>The <stype>black troopers</stype> of Queensland are a regiment of
aboriginal police, employed chiefly for dispersing wild aborigines who
encroach on sheep runs.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Trouper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>like a trooper</b></col>, <cd>with energy, endurance, or
enthusiasm; <as>as, to work <ex>like a trooper</ex></as>.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Troopfowl</ent>⟦br⟧
